{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id9c6e7018-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7","identifier":"/us/usc/t8/s1645"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1645"},"text":"§ 1645.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Qualifying quarters","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this chapter, in determining the number of qualifying quarters of coverage under title II of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s401"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 401","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] an alien shall be credited with—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id9c6e7019-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7","identifier":"/us/usc/t8/s1645/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" all of the qualifying quarters of coverage as defined under title II of the Social Security Act worked by a parent of such alien before the date on which the alien attains age 18, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id9c6e701a-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7","identifier":"/us/usc/t8/s1645/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" all of the qualifying quarters worked by a spouse of such alien during their marriage and the alien remains married to such spouse or such spouse is deceased.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"No such qualifying quarter of coverage that is creditable under title II of the Social Security Act for any period beginning after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1996","children":[],"tail":", may be credited to an alien under paragraph (1) or (2) if the parent or spouse (as the case may be) of such alien received any Federal means-tested public benefit (as provided under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1613"},"text":"section 1613 of this title","children":[],"tail":") during the period for which such qualifying quarter of coverage is so credited. Notwithstanding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s6103"},"text":"section 6103 of title 26","children":[],"tail":", the Commissioner of Social Security is authorized to disclose quarters of coverage information concerning an alien and an alien’s spouse or parents to a government agency for the purposes of this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id9c6e701b-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/193/tIV/s435"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–193, title IV, § 435","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-22"},"text":"Aug. 22, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2275"},"text":"110 Stat. 2275","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/tV/s5573"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, title V, § 5573","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/641"},"text":"111 Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id9c6e701c-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id9c6e701d-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id9c6e701e-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this title” meaning title IV of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/193"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–193","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-22"},"text":"Aug. 22, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2260"},"text":"110 Stat. 2260","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this chapter, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1183a"},"text":"section 1183a of this title","children":[],"tail":", and sections 611a and 1437y of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare, amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1383"},"text":"section 1383 of this title","children":[],"tail":", sections 32 and 6213 of Title 26, Internal Revenue Code, and sections 1436a and 1471 of Title 42, and enacted provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1183a"},"text":"section 1183a of this title","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s32"},"text":"section 32 of Title 26","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of title IV to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":". Title II of the Act is classified generally to subchapter II (§ 401 et seq.) of chapter 7 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id9c6e701f-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/s5573/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, § 5573(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted at end “Notwithstanding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s6103"},"text":"section 6103 of title 26","children":[],"tail":", the Commissioner of Social Security is authorized to disclose quarters of coverage information concerning an alien and an alien’s spouse or parents to a government agency for the purposes of this chapter.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/s5573/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, § 5573(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “before the date on which the alien attains age 18,” for “while the alien was under age 18,”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id9c6e7020-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id9c6e7021-3a6f-11f1-ace3-bb5201d4c7c7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1997 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33","children":[],"tail":" effective as if included in the enactment of title IV of the Personal Responsibility and Work Opportunity Reconciliation Act of 1996, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/193"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–193","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/s5582"},"text":"section 5582 of Pub. L. 105–33","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1367"},"text":"section 1367 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
